NEC Software Solutions | Version 1.4 | Release Date: March 2024

<text-box>
  <inline color="#07010a">This sheet allows users to view the number of individual children who were cautioned or sentenced within the selected period by ethnicity and gender. Services can see the  Current YOT ID and date of birth of individual children which can be further interrogated within case management systems</inline>
</text-box>

<text-box>This sheet allows users to view the number of outcomes by tier for children who were cautioned or sentenced within the selected period by ethnicity and gender. Services can see the  Current YOT ID and date of birth of individual children which can be further interrogated within case management systems.</text-box>

<text-box>This sheet allows users to view the number of outcomes by type of caution or sentence for children who were cautioned or sentenced within the selected period by ethnicity. Services can see the  Current YOT ID and date of birth of individual children which can be further interrogated within case management systems.</text-box>

<text-box>This sheet allows users to view the number of proven offences by gravity score for children who were cautioned or sentenced within the selected period by ethnicity. Services can see the  Current YOT ID and date of birth of individual children which can be further interrogated within case management systems.</text-box>

<text-box>This sheet allows users to view the number of proven offences by offence group for children who were cautioned or sentenced within the selected period by ethnicity and gender. Services can see the  Current YOT ID and date of birth of individual children which can be further interrogated within case management systems.</text-box>

<text-box>This sheet allows users to view the number of proven offences by gravity score for children who were cautioned or sentenced within the selected period by ethnicity and gender. Services can see the  Current YOT ID and date of birth of individual children which can be further interrogated within case management systems.</text-box>

<text-box>This sheet allows users to view the number of proven offences by offence group and gravity score for children who were cautioned or sentenced within the selected period by ethnicity. Services can see the  Current YOT ID and date of birth of individual children which can be further interrogated within case management systems.</text-box>
